  "prompt": "How do I remove a non-friend from Facebook messenger contact list?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, Facebook Messenger doesn't directly let you *remove* a non-friend from your contact list like you can delete a contact in your phone.  Since they've messaged you at some point, their profile is essentially associated with your Messenger account.  However, there are a few things you can do to minimize their visibility and interaction:\n\n**1. Archive the Conversation:**\n\n*   This is the simplest and most common solution. Archiving removes the conversation from your main inbox view.\n\n    *   **On Mobile:**\n        *   Find the conversation with the person.\n        *   Long-press (tap and hold) on the conversation.\n        *   A menu will appear. Tap \"Archive.\"\n\n    *   **On Desktop:**\n        *   Hover over the conversation in your inbox.\n        *   Click the three dots (More actions) that appear.\n        *   Select \"Archive Chat.\"\n\n    *   **Important:** Archiving doesn't delete the conversation. It simply hides it. If the person messages you again, the conversation will reappear in your inbox.\n\n**2. Ignore the Conversation:**\n\n*   This prevents you from receiving notifications about new messages from that person.\n\n    *   **On Mobile:**\n        *   Find the conversation.\n        *   Long-press on the conversation.\n        *   Tap \"Ignore Messages.\"\n\n    *   **On Desktop:**\n        *   Open the conversation with the person.\n        *   Click the person's name at the top of the chat window.\n        *   Scroll down and select \"Ignore Messages.\"\n\n    *   **Important:**  You will not receive notifications for new messages in this chat.  The other person will not know you've ignored them.  You can still read the messages if you open the chat (it will be in the \"Message Requests\" section).\n\n**3. Block the Person (Most Effective):**\n\n*   This is the most drastic measure. Blocking prevents the person from contacting you on Messenger and Facebook. They won't be able to see your profile, send you messages, or find you in searches.\n\n    *   **On Mobile:**\n        *   Find the conversation.\n        *   Tap on the person's name at the top of the chat.\n        *   Scroll to the bottom and tap \"Block.\"\n        *   You'll have the option to block them only on Messenger or also on Facebook.\n\n    *   **On Desktop:**\n        *   Open the conversation with the person.\n        *   Click the person's name at the top of the chat window.\n        *   Scroll down and select \"Block.\"\n        *   You'll have the option to block them only on Messenger or also on Facebook.\n\n    *   **Important:**  This is a permanent action unless you unblock them. They will not be notified that you blocked them, but they'll quickly realize they can no longer contact you.\n\n**4. Delete the Conversation (Less Effective for Long-Term Removal):**\n\n*   Deleting the conversation will remove it from your inbox. However, if they message you again, the conversation will reappear.\n\n    *   **On Mobile:**\n        *   Find the conversation.\n        *   Long-press on the conversation.\n        *   Tap \"Delete.\"\n\n    *   **On Desktop:**\n        *   Hover over the conversation in your inbox.\n        *   Click the three dots (More actions) that appear.\n        *   Select \"Delete Chat.\"\n\n    *   **Important:** Deleting only removes the conversation from *your* view. The other person still has their copy.\n\n**In summary:**\n\n*   **Archive:** Hides the conversation but it reappears if they message you again.\n*   **Ignore:** Stops notifications for the conversation, but you can still read messages.\n*   **Block:** Prevents all contact and interaction.\n*   **Delete:** Removes the conversation from your view, but it reappears if they message you again.\n\nThe best option depends on your desired level of interaction.  If you simply want to clean up your inbox, archiving or deleting the conversation might suffice. If you want to avoid receiving messages from them, ignoring is a good choice. If you want to completely sever contact, blocking is the most effective solution.\n",
